Populate Dictionary VideoComments Table 11
For VideoComments, we want the comment, who made the comment, as well as StudentUserId, DateCreated, and VideoId so that we can track comment metrics properly. We will be obtain these with the help of two OLE DB sources and the following merge statements. We are using the same table and view for these statements so that they will be filtered and later merged.
SELECT VideoId,Comment as Comments, UserFullName as Commenter
FROM [dnnuser].[UVG_Comment]
UNION ALL
SELECT VideoId,Instr_Comments as Comments, Instructor as Commenter
FROM [dbo].[vw_Homework_ALL]
WHERE VideoID IS NOT NULL
AND Instr_Comments IS NOT NULL

SELECT B.StudentUserID,A.VideoId,A.CreatedDate
FROM [dnnuser].[UVG_Comment] A
FULL OUTER JOIN [dbo].[vw_Homework_ALL] B
ON A.VideoID = B.VideoID
WHERE A.VideoId IS NOT NULL


FYI: Here are the mappings for the OLE DB Destination. There is no need to connect to CommentId and LastDateModified, because they will automatically be populated thanks to the Identity Insert included in the SQL file you downloaded.
